---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - ONPOINT" description="ONPOINT privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal data.">
  <Header client:load />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background pt-24 pb-16">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 sm:px-8">
      <header class="border-b border-border pb-8 mb-10">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-medium text-foreground">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: February 28, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            ONPOINT ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we handle your information when you visit our website or use our desktop application.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">2. Desktop Application</h2>
          <p>
            ONPOINT is a <strong class="text-foreground">local-first application</strong>. Your notes, files, and all content you create are stored exclusively on your device. We do not have access to your content, and no data from the desktop application is transmitted to our servers.
          </p>
          <p>The desktop application stores the following data locally on your machine:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Your notes</strong>: stored as files in a local vault directory you choose.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">App preferences</strong>: window state, sidebar layout, keyboard shortcuts, and theme settings stored in the app's local configuration directory.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not collect your name, email address, or any personal information through the desktop application. There are no user accounts, no telemetry, and no crash reporting.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">3. Website Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            Our marketing website (<a href="https://onpoint.sh" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline underline-offset-2">onpoint.sh</a>) uses <strong class="text-foreground">PostHog</strong>, a product analytics service, to understand how visitors interact with our site. PostHog may collect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Usage data</strong>: pages visited, clicks, scroll depth, and referring URLs.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Device data</strong>: browser type, operating system, screen resolution, and language preference.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Approximate location</strong>: derived from your IP address (not precise geolocation). Your IP address is not stored in its full form.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This data is used solely to improve our website and understand aggregate usage patterns. We do not use this data to identify or profile individual visitors.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">4. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
          <p>
            Our website uses cookies set by PostHog for analytics purposes. You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings. We also use your browser's local storage to remember your theme preference (light or dark mode). No other tracking technologies are used.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">5. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
          <p>To be explicit, we do <strong class="text-foreground">not</strong> collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Names, email addresses, or contact information</li>
            <li>Payment or financial data</li>
            <li>The content of your notes or files</li>
            <li>Precise geolocation data</li>
            <li>Data from the desktop application</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>
            We use PostHog (PostHog, Inc.) for website analytics. PostHog processes data on our behalf and is bound by their own <a href="https://posthog.com/privacy" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline underline-offset-2">privacy policy</a>. We do not sell or share your data with any other third parties.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Analytics data collected through PostHog is retained for a limited period to identify trends and improve our website. We do not retain analytics data longer than necessary for these purposes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">8. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Request access to any data we hold about you.</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data.</li>
            <li>Opt out of analytics by using browser settings or an ad blocker.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">9. Third-Party Links</h2>
          <p>
            Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to review their privacy policies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are not intended for users under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Your continued use of our services after any changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-foreground">12. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@onpoint.sh" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 underline underline-offset-2">privacy@onpoint.sh</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
